centurion
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a member of a Wellington rugby union club formed from senior or experienced players (orig. from past provincial representatives) to foster and encourage the game at all levels; ?a rugby player invited to play for centurion club; or to make up a special team; ? distinguish from barbarian [but check this term];
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: G.J.Griffiths notes: a player (particularly in Rugby) who has played 100 1st class games (in this example, limited to one team); used at least since the 1960s when centurions had become more common but before, too.
